            <title>[FELIX-4336] The use of inheritable thread locals in ThreadIO can cause problems</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4336</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The main problem is that if threads outlive the console that owns the stream, those threads will always read out write to closed streams.&lt;br/&gt;
The use of inherited thread local is fine but should be smarter.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
